  "text": "The hydrophobicity of a protein depends on the presence of hydrophobic residues in it. It has an important role in the protein folding and aggregation [CITATION_1] . The hydrophobicity helps the protein in proper folding which in turn helps in proper functioning of the protein. So hydrophobicity of the protein is an important characteristic of the protein sequence. Hydrophobicity was calculated using Kyte and Doolite Index [CITATION_2] . From the drug target dataset, the average hydrophobicity was found to be -0.299. Therefore, in the present study, the range of hydrophobicity in a protein to be a drug target was set to be -0.150 to -0.350.",
